Subject: RE: [T2] Rust Converter's Results and Finding's.

> Second, --hey--after you sand blast, wire wheel, or sand off 
> the rust---how in the heck does the pot holes get filled?
> 
> The rust converter isn't a high fill item--so the pot holes 
> won't get filled --- You can't spot putty or lay a light coat 
> of Bondo on them --the Bondo won't stick to the rust 
> converter--and the rust converter is made to bond / react to 
> the rusty metal-- a no win situation so the pot holes
> stay--


You can primer over the POR-15, but you must do it while the POR-15 is
still tacky. This might give you a better surface to work with.

